{
  "title": "ISic000019. Fragment of an inscription referencing one of the emperors styled Marcus Aurelius",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm, Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"imperial\" data-text=\"Imperatori · Caesari · Marco · Aurelio\"><span data-text=\"Imperatori\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"imperator\">Imp(eratori?)</span> · <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Caesari\"><span data-text=\"Caesari\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Caesar\">Caes(ari?)</span></span> · <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Marco\"><span data-text=\"Marco\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"Marcus\">M(arco?)</span></span> · <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Aurelio\"><span data-text=\"Aurelio\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"Aurelius\"><span class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">A͡u</span>ṛẹ[lio?</span></span></span>  <span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"Imperatori\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"imperator\">Imperatori</span>  <span data-text=\"Caesari\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Caesar\">Caesari</span>  <span data-text=\"Marco\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"Marcus\">Marco</span>  <span data-text=\"Aurelio\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"Aurelius\">Aurelio</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm, Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"imperial\" data-text=\"Imperatori · Caesari · Marco · Aurelio\"><span data-text=\"Imperatori\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"imperator\">IMP</span>·<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Caesari\"><span data-text=\"Caesari\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Caesar\">CAES</span></span>·<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Marco\"><span data-text=\"Marco\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"Marcus\">M</span></span>·<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Aurelio\"><span data-text=\"Aurelio\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"Aurelius\"><span class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">A͡U</span>..[...</span></span></span><span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Imperatori\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"imperator\">IMPERATORI</span><span data-text=\"Caesari\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Caesar\">CAESARI</span><span data-text=\"Marco\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"Marcus\">MARCO</span><span data-text=\"Aurelio\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"Aurelius\">AURELIO</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic000019_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo R. Henzel, 2016-11-07\" src=\"ISic000019_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000019.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo R. Henzel, 2016-11-07\" src=\"ISic000019-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text of ILPalermo (Bivona) checked against the photograph</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"1\">1: <span> Bivona: Auṛẹ; Mommsen: AV̂R </span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>As Bivona notes, Mommsen in CIL chose to unify this fragment with one recorded by Gualtherus and Fazello (ISic001896, on a piece of an architrave, re-used as a church step, and which read: IMP. M. AVRELIO . ANTONINO . AVG...). However. Torremuzza described that piece separately from this one, which he placed in the courtyard of the Palazzo Senatorio, and there seems no obvious reason to conflate them.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li></li><li> Castelli 1762 13 no.xxiv <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085</a>  </li><li> Mommsen 1883 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650789\" target=\"_blank\">7277</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589</a>  </li><li> Bivona 1970 19 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Tall and very narrow letters, fairly crudely carved, with AV in ligature.</p> Line 1  105  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
